      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That's a good start with the food and the vibe, but it feels a bit generic. I want to avoid the \"TV version\" of a Black family and get into the real grit of it. Like, for the tension in the scene—could you describe some of the common conflicts or typical arguments that might pop up during a dinner like that? Specifically regarding things like how they view authority or maybe some of the more \"intense\" personality traits you'd see in a scene like this?",
